Calera package store and I go way back.  Well, not really...but I popped into this location BEFORE I decided to move here.  We were scouting the area and I was intrigued by the idea of a wine boutique.  There was nothing like that available in Calera.  Shocker, right??  Any who, moving on....

Calera package store offers a variety of wines that you may or may not find in grocery stores. Today I bought two wines for my girl friend.  She walked in and they were sitting there waiting for her.  I recently bought a wine captain (not a fridge...totally different) and I need to fill it with wines that I can save and wine that I can drink. text: The service is good, but every single item is up charged by at least $10, if not $20 or even more. A 750 mL bottle of Maker’s Mark cost me over $50 which is absolutely ridiculous for something usually found in the upper $30’s. 750 mL normal Woodford reserve is $56 whereas it can be found in the mid to upper $30s at other stores in Birmingham as well. It is probably a result of where it is located in Mountain Brook that they raise the prices that much. I am assuming that the people who have left all of these positive reviews have enough money to not worry about the up-charge, but this review is for those of us who don’t. You may get superior service and selection here, but you also will most certainly get ripped off. I would suggest just going to your average ABC store around Birmingham instead for a good enough selection at a much lower price.

Full Review:
I just went here for the first time today. As in just left. I loved this place SO SO SO MUCH. I was telling myself I must do a review as soon as I get home. What this place has to offer is so much! I just bought soju from there! And it was not terribly price. The only place I could find it was at a Korean restaurant (that was called Kalim Garden. And I would buy unopened bottles from them. I also got 2 different bottles of sake. Which I couldn't be more happy about! There is White Claw here. They still have it in stock despite the fact that there is currently a shortage. The guy inside (I didn't get his name was so friendly. This is also a place you can get CBD & vape products. I actually bought a pack of prerolles hempettes. It looked like they have 4 brands to choose from. I have tried a lot of the hempette brands and listen to me!! - just buy the red pack. Stunna Bubba Kush. I have tried the other ones pure hemp is pretty good but there are a lot stems in it even tho they claim theres not, wild hemp brand is just...really tame. Flavor is worst than the "Pure Hemp" brand. So that's usually just what ive been forced to get around here. HOWEVER I am currently smoking one of these Stunnas. The flavor - very good. Would rate 4/5 bc its good but it is def no premium ish. The hit or miss about the staff has to do with pricing. Three out of the last five times I've been in there a product rings up more at the register than what's indicated on the pricing sticker (both on the shelf and attached to the product itself).
